  LunaGlass fingerprint — biometric-unlock affordance.

  FRAMELESS. The hexagon that used to live in this file was removed:
  the lock-screen button now supplies its own
  HexShape(56dp) wrapper, so baking a second hex in here produced a
  "hex inside a hex" nesting. This drawable is now PURELY the ridge
  glyph, meant to sit centred inside that button frame.

  The ridges are an original faceted trace, NOT the round-capped
  Material fingerprint and NOT a copy of any reference art:
    · A clean reference photo was thresholded, Zhang-Suen thinned to
      ridge CENTRELINES, the skeleton walked into polylines, spurs
      pruned, then Douglas-Peucker decimated so every ridge becomes a
      short chain of straight segments — angular facets, never curves
      ("No curves / LunaGlass angles"). 9 isolated sub-1.3u dash
      fragments from the thinning were dropped as noise; 46 ridge
      polylines remain.
    · strokeWidth 0.45 (viewport units) is the exact signed-off
      thickness ("PERFECT") — thin, crisp facets. Butt caps honour
      "No round-capped edges"; round joins keep the facet corners from
      spiking at small sizes.
  Stroked white so the call-site tint colours it (tinted AegisCyan on
  the lock screen); transparent fill. Registered as
  AegisIcons.Fingerprint.
-->
